qas.question: Who helped repress the supporters of the Constitution and was later executed for it?
What are the years from 1823-1833 called?
Who was the last person killed by the Inquisition?

context: A fervent follower of the absolutist cause, <a0_0>Elío<a0_0/> had played an important role in the repression of the supporters of the Constitution of 1812. For this, he was arrested in 1820 and executed in <a1_0>1822<a1_0/> <a2_0>by garroting<a2_0/>. Conflict between absolutists and liberals continued, and in the period of conservative rule called the <a3_0>Ominous Decade<a3_0/> (1823–1833), which followed the Trienio Liberal, there was ruthless repression by government forces and the Catholic Inquisition. The last victim of the Inquisition was <a4_0>Gaietà Ripoli<a4_0/>, a teacher accused of being a deist and a Mason who was hanged in Valencia in 1824.
